messages.message: <!here> after saving a sheet program, when I click on the ‘view file’ button in the success dialog, it takes me to the text editor instead of the sheet app. Is this expected behavior? https://dogfood.instabase.com/apps/sheet/dlluncor/tests/fs/Test%20Drive/tests/general/apps/sheet/out.ibocr#
not the expected behavior — @Jessica is there anything that might have changed here?
I also realize that I had read the test wrong last time, and might not have actually tested this last time, so may not be a new bug
I think it's opening it with Preview, not with Text Editor - so it is intended behavior. Do we want to change the behavior so that is you "Save as" it opens it up in Sheet, not in Preview?
oh i see. sorry didn’t know what that was called. as long it’s the expected behavior @dlluncor
If we decide we want it to behave differently we can change that though
yep. thanks for checking it out btw! and sorry for the confusion. I think it’s probably fine for now
ah its opening in Preview — that makes sense — sounds good
